pre-lamb shearing
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:the shearing of ewes in warm areas during winter [in order to lamb more easily].
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Flag: Farm Words
Domain:Rural
Region:[none]
See:pre-lamb shear (verb)
